# FlashBite identity service (port 3003) - login, refresh/logout (AT/RT hardening), JWKS, tenants.
# Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension and JetBrains HTTP Client.
# Prereqs:
#   pnpm dev:identity  +  pnpm seed:tenants  +  pnpm seed:users

@identityUrl = http://localhost:3003
@readUrl = http://localhost:3002
@seedPassword = devpassword

### Identity health - always open. Expect 200 { "status": "ok" }.
GET {{identityUrl}}/health

### Login as a berlin merchant. Expect 201 { accessToken, tokenType: "Bearer", expiresIn: 900 }.
# Sets the httpOnly refresh cookie (fb_rt) used by /auth/refresh.
# @name login
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "merchant@berlin.test",
  "password": "{{seedPassword}}"
}

###

### Login as a berlin customer.
# @name loginCustomer
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@berlin.test",
  "password": "{{seedPassword}}"
}

###

### Refresh the access token (sends the fb_rt cookie set by login). Expect a fresh accessToken.
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/refresh

###

### Logout (revokes the refresh token / family).
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/logout

###

### JWKS - public keys used to verify access tokens. Expect 200 { "keys": [ ... ] }.
# Current + previous kid are both published so in-flight ATs survive a key rotation.
GET {{identityUrl}}/.well-known/jwks.json

###

### Tenants (active catalog)
GET {{readUrl}}/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.accessToken}}

###
